article.description: Tahjai Teague tallied 18 points and 11 rebounds to carry Ball St. to a 75-54 win over Northern Illinois on Friday night.
article.headline: Teague leads Ball St. over N. Illinois 75-54
article.linkText: Teague leads Ball St. over N. Illinois 75-54
article.story: DEKALB, Ill. -- Tahjai Teague tallied 18 points and 11 rebounds to carry Ball St. to a 75-54 win over Northern Illinois on Friday night. Miryne Thomas had 14 points for Ball St. (18-13, 11-7 Mid-American Conference). Ishmael El-Amin added 12 points. Kyle Mallers had 12 points. The Huskies' 28.1 field goal percentage represented the worst mark by a Ball St. opponent this season. Eugene German had 17 points for the Huskies (18-13, 11-7). Trendon Hankerson added 12 points. The Cardinals improve to 2-0 against the Huskies for the season. Ball St. defeated Northern Illinois 63-59 on Feb. 11. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
